Here is an example of a function in python with a factorial time complexity O(n!):

```
def permutation(lst): 
    if len(lst) == 0: 
        return []
    elif len(lst) == 1: 
        return [lst]
    else:
        res = []
        for i in range(len(lst)):
            for j in permutation(lst[:i] + lst[i+1:]):
                res.append([lst[i]] + j)
        return res
```

This function takes a list as an input and returns a list of all possible permutations of the elements in the input list. The time complexity of this function is O(n!) because it generates all possible permutations of n elements, which is n! possible combinations.

